The Automation REST API uses the [standard HTTP status codes](https://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec10.html).

Responses that return an error status code (400 or 5xx) will include a standard error response body, similar to the following:
```json
{
  "errors": [
      {
          "id": "298f9da7-93e0-40d7-8a2d-e8e158996abc",
          "status": 400,
          "code": "some.error.code",
          "title": "Some error message",
          "field": "some[1].field"
      }
  ]
}
```
